    {
      "kind": "content",
      "content": [
        {
          "anchor": "discussion",
          "level": 2,
          "text": "Discussion",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "The default value of this property is "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": false,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/objectivec/yes"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": ", which specifies that the default camera controls are visible in the picker. Set it to "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": false,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/objectivec/no"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " to hide the default controls if you want to instead provide a custom overlay view using the "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": false,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/uikit/uiimagepickercontroller/1619113-cameraoverlayview"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " property. "
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "aside",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "inlineContent": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "In iOS 3.1.3 and earlier, hiding the default camera controls limits you to taking still pictures only, regardless of whether movie capture is available on the device."
                }
              ]
            }
          ],
          "style": "note",
          "name": "Note"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "If you set this property to "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": false,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/objectivec/no"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " and provide your own custom controls, you can take multiple pictures before dismissing the image picker interface. However, if you set this property to "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": false,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/objectivec/yes"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": ", your delegate must dismiss the image picker interface after the user takes one picture or cancels the operation."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "You can access this property only when the source type of the image picker is set to "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": false,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/uikit/uiimagepickercontrollersourcetype/uiimagepickercontrollersourcetypecamera"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": ". Attempting to access this property for other source types results in the throwing of an "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/foundation/nsinvalidargumentexception"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " exception. Depending on the value you assign to the "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/uikit/uiimagepickercontroller/1619173-mediatypes"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " property, the default controls display the still camera or movie camera interface, or a selection control that lets the user choose the picker interface."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
  ],
